RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 1 350 Y Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF TWO RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: XCELENTE driving, lasted. DIABOLICAL CLYDE hard fought, missed. BULLY GIRL strong finish. LUXURY PAINT fought gamely, out kicked.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 5600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF TWO RACES LIFETIME OR COLORADO BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY PAL prompted the pace from the two path down the backstretch, fell back on the turn but moved between horses nearing the quarter pole to take the lead and drew clear in mid stretch. IMPASSIONED CLAIM rushed up to take the clear lead entering the main track and held that position through the turn then was collared at the quarter pole and fought gamely to the eighth pole, tired but proved second best. CAPTAIN COMEBACK was off the pace in the three path through the turn then engaged the leader at the quarter pole and matched strides to the eighth pole but gave way and held on for the show. SHADYFIED raced near the back down the backstretch then made a mild bid on the turn but was not a threat. FRIENDLY FOE saved ground throughout to no avail. RI' PIN SNAP trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Impassioned Claim
ENTRY.COMMENT: rushed up, clear lead, collared 1/4p, gamely, tired, second best

ENTRY.NAME: Shadyfied
ENTRY.COMMENT: near back, mild bid, no threat,

ENTRY.NAME: Captain Comeback
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace 3p, engaged leader, match strides, gave way, held show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Special Weight Purse 9700. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOSPEL BONANZA pressed the pace from the three path down the backstretch then moved in to the two path on the turn to take the lead midway on the turn and drew off in the stretch. IZZY IN A TIZZY was hustled along to set the pace for a half then was collared in mid turn and proved to be second best. DOMERGOO was slightly rank early then made a rail bid on the backstretch and lacked a late response in the stretch. BRIGHT MIND was off slow then moved up from two or three wide on the backstretch but failed to sustain the bid. CORTE had brief early speed to the five furlong pole and retreated. THE O G had an awkward start, pulled up and vanned off.

ENTRY.NAME: The O G
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward start, pulled up, vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Izzy in a Tizzy
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled along, set pace, collared, second best,

ENTRY.NAME: Bright Mind
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, moved up 2-3w, failed to sustain bid,

ENTRY.NAME: Domergoo
ENTRY.COMMENT: rank early, rail bid, lacked late response,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Allowance Purse 12100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF TWO RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRECEDENT dueled for the early lead then settled off the pace around the turn on the inside, angled out to three wide into the stretch and dueled to deep stretch and cleared late. RIGHT TO SUE dueled for the lead to the half pole then vied for lead from the inside around the turn, dueled down the stretch and gave way grudgingly. LUCYS MAJOR MIRCLE broke out at the start, then prompted the pace to the half pole then fell back and saved ground around the turn, slipped through at the top of the stretch to be a game third. DRISKILL dueled for the lead from three wide then took the lead at the half pole, was collared at the eighth pole and tired. BRAVO KOLT pinched back at the start, moved up from three wide on the turn but never made a serious bid.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, prompt pace, fell back, slipped through, game third

ENTRY.NAME: Bravo Kolt
ENTRY.COMMENT: pinched back, trailed, moved up 3wturn, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Precedent
ENTRY.COMMENT: duel for lead, off pace inside, angle out 3w, stretch duel, clear

ENTRY.NAME: Right to Sue
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled for lead, vied inside, stretch duel, grudgingly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 6400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Colorado Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEW YEARS LOVE vied for the lead from between horses to the half pole then fell back off the pace, made a rebid at the top of the stretch and engaged the leader at the eighth pole, matched strides with the leader to deep stretch and drew clear in the final yards. MILLI STARR sprinted away to a clear lead through the turn then was headed and matched strides with outside rival to deep stretch, weakened but was a clear second. DOZO pressed the pace from three wide to the half pole then settled off the pace around the turn and flattened out. RIVER LIBERTY was void of speed on the backstretch then made a mild three or four wide bid on the turn but faltered. SWEET TATUM tracked the leaders from mid pack but was not a threat. HIGH VALUE TARGET remained back.

ENTRY.COMMENT: sprinted away, headed, matched strides, clear second

ENTRY.NAME: New Years Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied for lead, engaged leader, match strides, cleared late

ENTRY.NAME: Dozo
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, off pace, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Tatum
ENTRY.OWNER: Rushton Stacey Eskew Stuart and Alfrey Vance
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, middle of pack, no threat,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 75. Starter Allowance Purse 5200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $2500 OR LESS IN 2022-2023. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OPTIMAL went to the front to set all the pace and drew off in the stretch to prove best. JIMBO'S BIZ prompted the early pace the fell back off the pace but was no match for the winner. GRAN EDITION raced in the middle of the pack from off the rail then moved out to four wide in upper stretch for a late run and was a clear third. PODEROSO EQUS raced near the back on the backstretch then moved up and went between horses at the quarter pole but was out kicked in the stretch. RANDOM AFFAIR saved ground on the backstretch then made a rail bid on the turn and flattened out. THORNISH tracked the leaders to the quarter pole and gave way. LIL LATIGO had no speed and was always back.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ARAPAHOE PARK RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON WINNERS OF A RACE IN 2023 OR NON WINNERS OF FOUR RACES LIFETIME. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KELLER'S GOLD went to a pressured lead to mid turn then pulled away, geared down in late stretch and held on. HEY NOW raced in the middle of the pack through the turn then moved to four wide in upper stretch, made a late gain on the leader to be a clear second. RONAMO raced in the middle of the pack, moved out to five wide in upper stretch to just get up for the show. TRICKY LEE saved ground through the turn then moved out to three wide in upper stretch and maneuvered through traffic in the stretch and just missed the show. ONE STEP AWAY was forwardly placed to the turn then made a bid on the turn and was out finished in the stretch drive. THIRD WHEEL trailed the field on the backstretch then made a rail bid through the turn and improved position in the stretch. GUNSLINGERS LEGACY was off the pace to mid turn and weakened. LAUNCHED pressed the pace to mid turn and gave way. JU JU GUY was never a threat. HAWKWOOD remained back.

ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, bid turn, out finished

ENTRY.NAME: Hey Now
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 4wupper, late gain, clear second
